public interface USKCallback

USK callback interface. Used for subscriptions to the USKManager, and extended for USKFetcher callers.

Method Detail

onFoundEdition

void onFoundEdition(long l,
                    USK key,
                    com.db4o.ObjectContainer container,
                    ClientContext context,
                    boolean metadata,
                    short codec,
                    byte[] data,
                    boolean newKnownGood,
                    boolean newSlotToo)
Found the latest edition.

Parameters:
l - The edition number.
key - A copy of the key with new edition set
newKnownGood - If the highest known good edition (which has actually been fetched with what it pointed to) has increased. Otherwise, the highest known SSK slot has been increased, from which searches will start, but we do not know whether it can actually be fetched successfully.
newSlotToo - If newKnownGood is set, this indicates whether it is also a new highest known SSK slot. If newKnownGood is not set, there is always a new highest known SSK slot.

Priority at which the polling should run when starting, or immediately after making some progress. See RequestScheduler for constants.
